rcpm
----

A simple package manager written in plan9's rc[1] shell.


Status
------
[x] build packages
[ ] conflict handling
[x] fetch tarballs/submodules
[ ] handle dependencies
[x] print package manifest
[x] print package version/list of installed packages
[x] remove packages
[ ] update out-of-date pacakges
[ ] ...


Layout
------
$pkg/
	build
	src (if using submodule)
	sha256 (not present if using submodule)
	url (not if using submodule)
	ver


Requirements
------------
- rc (Most implementations should work)
- POSIX utilities
- git (optional, but required for submodule support)
- pax


[1] http://doc.cat-v.org/plan_9/2nd_edition/papers/rc
[2] https://github.com/dylanaraps/kiss
[3] https://github.com/oasislinux/oasis
